messages.message:
Is anyone else encountering issues with `pre-commit` hooks?

https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/71336/files#r2144380870

```webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/BuildApp/aihub-project-migration.spec.ts:27:10 - error TS2305: Module '"../ConverseApp/utils"' has no exported member 'expandNavbar'.

27 import { expandNavbar } from '../ConverseApp/utils';```

at the time when `aihub-project-migration` was written, `expandNavbar` existed in that file (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/a437fdf5c7d5da36fbad11b4f83f83c0f3b3cd13/webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/ConverseApp/utils.ts#L16-L18)

but after the new top nav  (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-2907)was launched, `expandNavbar` is no longer necessary

can you just delete the lines that call `expandNavbar`? the workspace is now always shown in the top nav
